M
f_M
 E(g(M))=\iint_{[0,1]^2}g(|x_1-x_2|)\mathrm dx_1\mathrm dx_2=2\iint_{[0,1]^2}g(y-x)\mathbf 1_{x\lt y}\mathrm dy\mathrm dx. 
 0\lt x\lt y\lt1\iff0\lt u\lt1,\ 0\lt v\lt1-u, 
 E(g(M))=2\int_0^1g(u)\int_0^{1-u}\mathrm dv\,\mathrm du=\int_0^1g(u)(2(1-u))\,\mathrm du. 
 f_M(u)=2(1-u)\mathbf 1_{[0,1]}(u). 
